  <statement>
      
                <p>Firas has decided to establish a scholarship for the next 30 years with $230,000. If the university has access to 3.2% interest compounded annually, how much can be given out each year?
                </p>
      
      <p>

      </p>
      
  </statement>
    
  <answer>
      
              <p>
              The university can give <m>\frac{P_0 (\frac{r}{n})}{1 - (1+\frac{r}{n})^{-nt}} = \frac{230000(\frac{0.032}{1})}{1 - (1 + \frac{0.032}{1})^{-1 \cdot 30}} = </m> $18,935.15 every year.
            </p>
  </answer>
</exercise>
